Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) is one of the mixed ionic electronic conductors that could be feasibly used in an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: In this study, LSCF and NiO were prepared using a modified Pechini method and calcined at three different temperatures ranging from 600 degrees C to 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The prepared LSCF was added with 5% NiO (denoted as LSCF-NiO) as cathode material.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The physical and electrical properties of the prepared cathode were investigated.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction data revealed that at calcination temperatures of 600 degrees C-900 degrees C, NiO and LSCF maintained their phases and conformed the cubic structure for NiO and orthorhombic structure for LSCF.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The calcination temperature showed significant influence on the particle size of the prepared LSCF-NiO, as depicted by scanning electron microscopy (SEM), and all the powders reached a nanoscale size.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The SEM cross section of LSCF-NiO layer on gadolinium-doped cerium electrolyte showed an acceptable percentage of cathode porosity and good adhesivity at cathode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Energy dispersive X-ray analysis further verified the purity of the samples.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Brunauer-Emmett-Teller surface area analysis was conducted, and the results revealed a trend of decreased surface area with an increase in calcining temperature.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: At an operating temperature of 800 degrees C, the electrochemical impedance spectroscopic results showed that LSCF-NiO 800 had a low Rp of 0.07 omega cm2, and its Ea was found to be 159.5 kJ/mol, indicating that LSCF-NiO 800 is fit to be used as cathode material in IT-SOFC application.
Titulo: Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Reaction of LSCF Cathode Material Added with NiO for IT-SOFC
